teelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1111.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: MA</span><hr size=1> /throws the dog a bone... But Brutal is 100% correct - trying stuff yourself is the most fun.<br><br>Double Secret Probation l337 Trak Hints: <br><br>1.) Get the raid decent PR, have shaman make poison potions ahead of time as required.  Insta cure poison items aren't bad either.<br>2.) Clear in past jugs/reets, hold the raid up back in the jug tunnels out of sight from the bridge.<br>3.) Pull Protector - use someone with bind sight to help coordinate the best time to do that.  Trak himself moves every 20? minutes or so.  Also pull and time the regular juggs as they path out.<br>4.) Ignore Jumpy (enc-frog and his guards up) just hug left rock.<br>5.) Rush trak when hes at the back of the lair, might try to use a DA pally.<br>6.) Kill fast, healers cover group - don't worry about any sort of MT/CHCycle goofyness.<br>7.) Group the leading mele damage dealers with a coh mage for when Trak TT's them to the shroom room.  If thats not an option, make sure they know to run to the zone-out porter pad.<br>8.) If your aggregate DPS is low, expect Trak to gate.<br>9.) Don't forget to cure dot after he dies.<br>10.) Move the raid to the back of the lair to avoid jug adds while everyone is recovering.<br><br>11.) Loot Useless Bard bp<br>12.) Loot Useless Rogue bp<br>13.) Loot Trak Tooth for (near)Useless VP keyed zone quest.<br><br>The above was valid 2 years ago, now you could take 12 people up and just bum-rush the whole lair at once.<br><br><br><br>  <p><center> <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=132705 >Sumill - Sanne</a><br>60 Warlord - Magician<br>Xev<br><a href=http://www.alteravita.org>Altera Vita<br></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ez